			 sys.dm_db_log_stats (Transact-SQL) 

					 
								 05/17/2017 
							 2 minutes to read 
							 
								 Contributors 
								 
											 
											 
								 

					 In this article 
						 THIS TOPIC APPLIES TO: SQL Server (starting with 2017) Azure SQL Database Azure SQL Data Warehouse  Parallel Data Warehouse  Returns summary level attributes and information on transaction log files of databases. Use this information for monitoring and diagnostics of transaction log health.    
   Transact-SQL Syntax Conventions    
 Syntax 
  sys.dm_db_log_stats ( database_id )
 Arguments 
 database_id  | NULL |  DEFAULT 
 Is the ID of the database.  database_id  is  int . Valid inputs are the ID number of a database,  NULL , or  DEFAULT . The default is  NULL .  NULL  and  DEFAULT  are equivalent values in the context of current database. The built-in function  DB_ID  can be spe